The Embargo is an example of government being out of touch with reality. The Embargo was signed into effect by JFK in 1962, 50+ years ago and at that time had a purpose. But JFK also took care of himself by having Pierre Salinger go find 1,200 Cuban cigars for his private use, which by the way were Upmann's, his favorite brand. As soon as he was certain that Salinger had obtained the cigars he pulled out of his desk Proclamation 3447 and signed it. It's time for Obama to reverse the Embargo & open up trade with Cuba. I like many others have no problems in obtaining Cuban cigars and the Embargo is a joke.......

After many months of planning, working with Jonathan Drew , and MANY others, I'm VERY EXCITED TO ANNOUNCE:

On May 25, 2013 in San Antonio Texas at JoSabis we will be having the First EVER CATS FESTIVAL and DE Sponsored Op:CFW 
Cigars for Warriors!! After Hours Party!! Going to be 3 of the absolute best companies in the business going to Sponsor it, Drew Estate with Jonathan Drew, Padron with Jorge Padron, and Jay Lundy, and Tom Poehler of AkaCigars AmericanKickass. Will be a goodies from each of them!!


Additional we will be having Booths from our CATS Vendors there running 1-3 CATS Specials each!!!!! There will be Free Dinner, and Music, working on figuring a way to get free Booze, but there will be 2 large Bars there either way. Going to be a Texas Rustic and Military Theme. With Special Guest Stars, Op:CFW and CRA!!

After the Festival at the same location all our Sponsors and Vendors will close shop and we will have a After Hours Party in support of Op:CIgars For Warriors sponsored by Drew Estate!!!! This is to have alot of fun, communion between our brother and sisters, dancing, and to promote Op:CFW. There will be lots of raffles and other surprises.

I Will announce when tickets go on Sale, very soon. Most like Middle of 1January-1st of May. Still working out details on that. Tickets will be VERY cheap, no 200$ price tag for this, this is CATS!!!

As we continue I will keep releasing information. Im working with 3 hotels for special prices. One of them is insanely nice but mid town, other two are regular Motels/hotels but they are very close with shuttle bus.

Chose May 25 memorial Weekend to show Troops alot of Love!! Plus I know this is the time of year alot of folks take vacations. Instead of being a negative, I cant think of a better place in the U.S. To take a Vacation. Water Parks, Six Flags, the River Walk, Museams galore, the Steeple, etc etc etc. It is a vacation paradise, so bring your Whole Family!!!

data.name:
It has been said that Abraham Lincoln enjoyed a good cigar from time to time and that prior to presenting speeches to the masses, he would take one of his wife’s, Mary Todd Lincolns long hat pins and insert one into the center of his cigars. This would add additional strength to the cigar ash, hence preventing it from falling from the cigar during his speech.

As the masses would gather, Lincoln would hold his cigar proudly as he moved his hand around for all to see. He would preach his thoughts and rally his crowds for votes on many issues as the cigar ash grew longer and longer. 

To the crowds wonder and bewilderment, the ash would seem to take on a life of its own. Many in the crowd would talk amongst themselves saying “how is that possible, that ash just won’t fall”. 

As Lincoln continued to speak, the crowd continued to grow, and all would stare in an almost hypnotic state at his cigar, mesmerized to this site and basically deaf to the words. 

At the conclusion of the speech, Mr. Lincoln would hold his hand with the cigar high up and shout “gentleman, do I have your vote?” and the masses would in unison shout “YES”, not really knowing what they were agreeing to, as most of the speech was never heard.

To think, that his famous Emancipation Proclamation speech, and that the abolishment of slavery, may have come down to a “fine piece of tobacco”, and a hat pin.

Now since there is no real way to say if this has any truth, it is one fine piece of politics.

The story behind this cigar creation is interesting.  Cuban born actor, Andy Garcia when filming the movie "The Lost City", wanted to film part of it in the Chateau de la Fuente plantation.  It was off season for the tobacco, so they planted a crop to grow and fill the fields for viewing in the film.  This crop was a one time creation and was used for this amazing cigar: thus the quality and the price.
I have had this one aging since July 2012

Dear Fellow Smokers,
We invite you to join us at Black Smokers RetreatTM, an annual gathering of cigar smokers from across the country. Where it is all about the smoke!
Our first retreat will be held in Las Vegas, Nevada. Shuttle services will be provided to and from sponsored events.
We will begin the weekend on Friday with a Welcome Reception, followed by a Cigar Lounge Crawl,to some of the hottest smoke spots in Vegas. Our host hotel will be home to our Smokers Tent, a place to fellowship and smoke. The Smokers tent is scheduled to be open from 10:00pm to 2:00am on Friday and Saturday.
On Saturday from 10:00am to 1:00pm, please plan to attend the Smokers Expo, where vendors from across the country will showcase the latest smokes and gadgets for the cigar connoisseur. We then welcome you to join, Cigar Mike at his monthly Smokers Retreat from 3:00pm to 8:00pm.
Sunday will end our weekend with a farewell Bruch and awards ceremony, honoring those fellow smokers who have elevated the smoking game to the next level.
Join us as we Smoke the Lights Out in Las Vegas, Nevada. In the spirit of the smoke,
